OL,3,CSummer in Svalbard: Ice scientists
OL,4,Cfighting against warmest season on
OL,5,Crecord
OL,7,FCenturies ago this 3,000 year-old
OL,8,Fglacier touched the fjord. Now it's a
OL,9,Ffive kilometre walk to get there.
OL,11,F"If you look at this ice you can see
OL,12,Fbubbles. Bubbles which contain a
OL,13,Fglimpse of our past," Dorothea tells
OL,14,Fme.
OL,16,F"These bubbles contain gas from our
OL,17,Fatmosphere hundreds of years ago. It
OL,18,Fturns out the deeper you drill, the
OL,19,Ffurther into our past you can see."
