OL,3,CSummer in Svalbard: Ice scientists
OL,4,Cfighting against warmest season on
OL,5,Crecord
OL,7,FIce cores in Antarctica - which are at
OL,8,Fleast 800,000 years old show how
OL,9,Fspikes in carbon dioxide mirror spikes
OL,10,Fin temperature.
OL,12,FCurrently the world is getting warmer
OL,13,Fwith no signs of that peaking. Carbon
OL,14,Fdioxide levels, fueled by man-made
OL,15,Fgases, are at unprecedented levels.
OL,17,FThe ice here is losing 1.2 metres of
OL,18,Fthickness a year - twice the rate of
OL,19,Fthe 80s.
