OL,3,CSummer in Svalbard: Ice scientists
OL,4,Cfighting against warmest season on
OL,5,Crecord
OL,7,FHe tells me: "The important thing
OL,8,Fabout that is that the amount of
OL,9,Fcarbon that's within the soil of the
OL,10,FArctic is about three times the amount
OL,11,Fthat's present in the Earth's
OL,12,Fatmosphere.
OL,14,F"So if all of that carbon gets burned
OL,15,Foff into atmosphere, that's a
OL,16,Fpotentially very, very bad situation."
OL,18,FThese islands are only the size of
OL,19,FScotland - but there's enough glacial
OL,20,Fice here to raise global sea levels
OL,21,F1.7 centimetres if they melt.
